## 10. Key UX flows

### Flow A — Quick expense (solo or split)

1. FAB → Quick Expense (or Income)
1. Enter amount (rupee input → converted to paise on save)
1. Pick category, date (default today), optional note/photo/tags
1. If expense: payer defaults to “me”. Tap to change or add co-payers.
1. Tap “Split” → pick split type → assign members. Live remainder shown.
1. Save (disabled until invariant met) → txn appears immediately in group + dashboard.

### Flow B — Itemized bill (restaurant, grocery, any large multi-item bill)

1. FAB → Itemized Bill
1. Add line items: name, qty, unit price. Subtotal shown live.
1. Add tax/tip/discount (flat or %).
1. Tap each item → quick-assign: tap member avatar(s) to assign. Per-person totals update live.
1. Tap “Split the rest equally” for any unassigned items.
1. Next screen: set payer(s).
1. Review: per-person totals, payer amounts, invariant status.
1. Save (blocked until Σ paid == Σ share).

### Flow C — Settle up (per group or global)

1. Group Detail → Balances tab → “Settle Up” OR Dashboard → global settle-up.
1. Simplified payment list shown: “You pay GF ₹250”, “Rahul pays you ₹1,200”.
1. Tap “Mark as Paid” on any row → creates a `settlement` txn → balance updates to 0.
1. Settlement history visible in txn list (kind = settlement).

### Flow D — Edit recurring transaction

1. Tap any recurring txn → Edit.
1. Prompt: “Edit this instance only” or “Edit this and all future instances.”
1. “This instance”: saves a new one-off txn for this date with override values; recurrence continues for future dates.
1. “All future”: updates recur_ fields on the original; past materialized instances unchanged.

