### 19.2 Component catalogue

**`components/ui/`** (generic, no domain knowledge):
`AmountText` (paise→₹, `rounded` + `fit` props), `Card`, `PrimaryButton`, `SecondaryButton`,
`PressableScale`, `FadeIn`, `Skeleton`, `EmptyState`, `ScreenHeader`, `SettingsRow`,
`FilterBar`, `SheetModal` (keyboard-safe bottom sheet), `DatePickerSheet` (JS calendar), `FAB`.

**`components/finance/`** (domain widgets):
`BudgetBar`, `TransactionRow`, `BalanceRow`, `CategoryChip`, `CategoryPicker`,
`SettleSheet` (partial-settlement amount editor), `MemberAvatar`.

**`components/system/`** (app shell):
`Onboarding` (swipe carousel), `OnboardingGate`, `LockGate` (Face ID), `PrivacyScreen` (app-switcher mask).

Rules: import shared tokens from `../tokens`; `ui` never imports from `finance`/`system`;
`finance`/`system` may import from `ui`.

### 19.3 Data model (current)

All of §3 plus:

```sql
-- budget_group adds:
is_personal    INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,   -- the seeded single-user space
simplify_debt  INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,   -- per-group Balances toggle

-- txn adds:
recur_state TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active' CHECK(recur_state IN ('active','paused','ended')),
tz          TEXT,        -- IANA timezone captured at create
lat REAL, lng REAL, place_label TEXT,   -- optional, user-controlled location

-- category_budget adds:
cadence TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'monthly' CHECK(cadence IN ('once','daily','monthly','yearly')),

-- new table:
CREATE TABLE audit_log (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY, entity_type TEXT, entity_id TEXT, group_id TEXT,
  action TEXT, summary TEXT, amount INTEGER, created_at INTEGER NOT NULL
);
```

Migrations run idempotently in `openDB()` (try/catch `ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN`).

### 19.4 Budget model (v5)

Each budgeted category has ONE line: `{ cadence, amount }`. Spending is compared within the
current window of its cadence (today / this month / this year / all-time for `once`). Lines are
persistent templates — daily/monthly/yearly roll forward automatically; `once` never resets.
Budget cadence is **independent of transaction recurrence**.

### 19.5 Transaction kinds & flows

- `expense` / `income` (quick or itemized) · `settlement` (system: settle-up + transfers).
- Edit: quick expenses/income editable via `txn/[id]` → quick editor. **Itemized bills are
  not in-place editable** (would orphan line items) — shown read-only, delete + re-add to change.
- Recurring rules editable from the Recurring screen (preserves recurrence).
- Every mutation writes an `audit_log` row; per-txn history shows on the detail screen.

### 19.6 Privacy, location, identity

- `PrivacyScreen` masks content on background (toggle: Settings → Privacy, default on).
- Location capture is opt-in (Settings toggle, default off), reverse-geocoded to a place name,
  via `expo-location` (requires `NSLocationWhenInUseUsageDescription` in Info.plist).
- Each person carries a unique identifier (email/mobile) for future groups/sync; offline in v1.

### 19.7 Outstanding roadmap (not yet built)

Budget sections layer; budget filtering; multi-user / split income.

**v2 / next version:** a free in-app map (Mapbox free tier / OpenStreetMap / react-native-maps)
on the transaction detail to show where a transaction was made, using the stored lat/lng.

